    {
      "parameters": {
        "jsCode": "const company = $json.company_name || '';\nconst atsType = $json.ats_type || '';\n\nif (atsType === 'greenhouse' && Array.isArray($json.jobs)) {\n  return $json.jobs.map(job => ({\n    json: {\n      date: new Date().toISOString().split('T')[0],\n      signal_type: 'Hiring',\n      name: '',\n      company: company,\n      role: job.title || '',\n      source_url: job.absolute_url || '',\n      location: job.location?.name || '',\n      context: `${company} is actively hiring for: ${job.title}`,\n      outreach_draft: '',\n      status: 'new'\n    }\n  }));\n}\n\nif (atsType === 'lever' && Array.isArray($json)) {\n  return $json.map(job => ({\n    json: {\n      date: new Date().toISOString().split('T')[0],\n      signal_type: 'Hiring',\n      name: '',\n      company: company,\n      role: job.text || '',\n      source_url: job.hostedUrl || '',\n      location: job.categories?.location || '',\n      context: `${company} is hiring for: ${job.text}`,\n      outreach_draft: '',\n      status: 'new'\n    }\n  }));\n}\n\nreturn [];\n```\n\n---\n\n### Node 8 — Filter Roles (IF Node)\n\n- Node type: **IF**\n- Condition: `{{ $json.role }}` **matches regex**\n- Regex value:\n```\n  (?i)(content|growth|marketing|seo|social|brand|copywriter|community|demand|automation|ai|web)"
      },
